abstract: |
  FIRE-EDGE is a low-cost augmented reality (AR) system designed to enhance
  firefighter safety in smoke-filled environments. The system integrates edge
  AI processing on NVIDIA Jetson Xavier NX with multi-sensor fusion (thermal
  camera, LiDAR, IMU, ultrasonic) to provide real-time fire detection and
  drift-resistant indoor navigation. Leveraging YOLOv8 for object detection
  and a Kalman filter for sensor fusion, the system achieves 85% mAP@0.5
  accuracy with 35ms latency, while maintaining a total hardware cost under
  $2,500. This represents a significant improvement over cloud-based systems
  that suffer from high latency (>500ms) and cost barriers (>$10,000).

