  abstract: |
    Firefighters face life-threatening challenges in smoke-filled environments,
    with disorientation contributing to 28% of fatalities. This paper presents
    FIRE-EDGE, a low-cost augmented reality (AR) system integrating edge AI
    and multi-sensor fusion. Leveraging YOLOv8 for fire detection and a Kalman
    filter for navigation, the system achieves 85% mAP@0.5 accuracy with 35ms
    latency on an NVIDIA Jetson Xavier NX. Simulations in ROS/Gazebo demonstrate
    a 2.16% improvement over baseline models, offering a sustainable solution
    for firefighter safety.

